cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with reducing the computational cost of training neural networks. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it specifically deals with neural network training. Additionally, since the paper uses the MNIST dataset, it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves optimizing the precision of numerical values, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
